cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SI 

This paper deals with transfer learning methods for improving prediction of infection from symptom data in multiple types of health care data. The paper discusses the challenges of using symptom data from varied studies in aggregate, and investigates in which conditions specific transfer learning and domain adaptation methods may perform better on symptom data. This work involves machine learning techniques and data analysis, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
